=== 08_three_mechanisms ===
======================================================================
EXAMPLE 8: Three PyTorch Mechanisms for Compliance
Abstract claim: "Dispatcher, custom Autograd functions, and the hook system"
======================================================================

Subject IDs (hashed for GDPR Art.17): ['sub_fe3cc27c1403', 'sub_7e1732273120', 'sub_a3c86f4c5b95', 'sub_1ef49392c2fb', 'sub_167ab411965b']

═══ MECHANISM 1: Forward Hooks (register_forward_hook) ═══
Use case: Audit logging — EU AI Act Article 12
Hook audit trail: 15 entries recorded
  #0    0                                        Linear       (5, 32)          ec339d45…
  #7    1                                        ReLU         (5, 32)          6d4afb8d…
  #14   2                                        Linear       (5, 2)           3f66af24…
✅ Chain integrity verified

═══ MECHANISM 2: Dispatcher (__torch_function__) ═══
Use case: Operator-level monitoring — invisible to model code
Dispatcher log: 3 tensor operations intercepted
  linear: 2 calls
  relu: 1 call
This logging required ZERO changes to model code

═══ MECHANISM 3: Custom Autograd Function (ProvenanceLinear) ═══
Use case: Data provenance through backpropagation — GDPR Article 17
Provenance log: 1 gradient update tracked
  Gradient influenced by subjects (hashed IDs): ['sub_fe3cc27c1403', 'sub_7e1732273120', 'sub_a3c86f4c5b95', 'sub_1ef49392c2fb', 'sub_167ab411965b']
  Gradient norm: 12.6491

If 'sub_fe3cc27c1403' requests erasure (GDPR Art. 17), we know exactly
which gradients their data influenced — enabling targeted unlearning.

Note: 'Experimental' means ProvenanceLinear only covers layers *explicitly*
  wrapped with it. Upstream layers use standard autograd — their provenance
  is NOT tracked. Full graph coverage would require wrapping every layer,
  which is currently impractical for deep models.

Three mechanisms demonstrated:
  Hooks:      Module-level audit logging  (15 entries — production-ready)
  Dispatcher: Operator-level monitoring   (3 ops — zero model changes)
  Autograd:   Gradient provenance tracking (1 records — experimental)
All three use NATIVE PyTorch APIs. No framework modifications needed.

Abstract claim: "Dispatcher, custom Autograd functions, and the hook system"
  ✅ Hooks:      15 entries, root_hash=3f66af244af6…
  ✅ Dispatcher: 3 ops intercepted, 0 model changes
  ✅ Autograd:   1 gradient provenance records

